$lang['forense']['content_11'] = "Evidence of Extreme Hardship to prevent deportation - An extreme hardship waiver in allows an immigration judge (IC) or other U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Service (USCIS) adjudicator the discretion to suspend removal (i.e. stop deportation) of an immigrant respondent who otherwise would be deported for a violation of immigration law. The basis for this legal action can include the adversity it would cause to U.S. Citizen or legal permanent resident spouse, children, or parents.";
